ned%20cancer%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20go%20from%20fifth%20to%20first%20place%20over%20the%20course%20of%20about%20two%20decades%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20typical%20in%20cancer%20research%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%20It's%20remarkable%20it%20all%20happened%20within%20the%20lifespan%20of%20her%20young%20adult%20daughter%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reasons%20for%20such%20a%20rapid%20shift%20are%20complex.%20While%20the%20rate%20of%20aggressive%20colon%20cancer%20cases%20has%20been%20going%20up%2C%20doctors%20have%20been%20getting%20better%20at%20treating%20and%20preventing%20other%20deadly%20cancers.%20Plus%2C%20lung%20cancer%20deaths%20plummeted%2C%20as%20people%20quit%20smoking%20en%20masse.%20Breast%20cancer%20is%20still%20the%20leading%20cause%20of%20cancer%20death%20in%20women%20under%2050%2C%20when%20men%20are%20left%20out%20of%20the%20equation%2C%20but%20the%20number%20of%20women%20dying%20of%20breast%20cancer%20every%20year%20has%20also%20gone%20down%20steadily%20since%20the%20mid-1990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20aren't%20exactly%20sure%20why%20colon%20cancer%20death%20rates%20are%20soaring%2C%20but%20point%20to%20a%20likely%20mix%20of%20complex%20factors%20influencing%20our%20environment%2C%20our%20genetics%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-so-many-young-people-getting-colon-cancer-answer-infancy-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eearly%20life%20exposures%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20baby's%20first%20months%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20womb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2213db559f-a5fc-4722-a2ae-92734d942835%5C%22%3EA%20healthy%20diet%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20be%20enough%20to%20stop%20colon%20cancer%2C%20but%20regular%20colonoscopies%20can%20prevent%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrevention%20isn't%20as%20simple%20as%20the%20old%20standard%20advice%20to%20eat%20a%20healthy%20diet%20and%20get%20enough%20exercise%2C%20though%20those%20factors%20are%20still%20part%20of%20the%20equation.%20The%20air%20we%20breathe%2C%20the%20foods%20we%20consume%2C%20and%20the%20movement%20we%20do%20all%20play%20a%20role%2C%20but%20there%20seems%20to%20also%20be%20an%20element%20of%20luck%20involved.%20For%20example%2C%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fidentical-twins-young-colon-cancer-diagnosis-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etwin%20may%20get%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20another%20shows%20no%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%2C%20it's%20still%20a%20chance%20event%2C%26quot%3B%20oncologist%20Tim%20Cannon%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECannon%20has%20treated%20several%20young%2C%20fit%20colon%20cancer%20patients%20who've%20died%20from%20aggressive%2C%20late-stage%20forms%20of%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20steepest%20rise%20in%20young%20colon%20cancer%20patients%20has%20been%20among%20people%20just%20starting%20adulthood%2C%20young%20patients%20in%20their%2020s%20and%2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20get%20more%20treatment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20yet%20they're%20not%20living%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Kimmie%20Ng%2C%20director%20of%20Dana-Farber's%20Young-Onset%20Colorectal%20Cancer%20Center%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20a%20few%20key%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-people-cancer-crisis-risk-tips-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epieces%20of%20advice%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Everyone%20should%20start%20getting%20colonoscopies%20at%20age%2045.%20They%20aren't%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fpost%2Fpreview%3Fstories%26post_id%3D697a66a193348c2e43148c17%26bust-capi%3D%26skip_transform%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escreening%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20are%20also%20intestinal%20housecleaning%20measures%2C%20designed%20to%20remove%20precancerous%20polyps%20before%20cancer%20develops.%20Eat%20plenty%20of%20fiber%2C%20especially%20from%20foods%20like%20leafy%20greens%2C%20other%20vegetables%2C%20and%20whole%20grains.%20And%20if%20you%20see%20blood%20in%20the%20toilet%2C%20or%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-football-player-stabbing-stomach-pain-stage-4-colon-cancer-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epersistent%20stomach%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20weeks%20and%20weeks%20that%20will%20not%20go%20away%2C%20get%20it%20checked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1769682721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F697a7524a645d11881882e42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Experts%20say%20they're%20stunned%20by%20how%20quickly%20colon%20cancer%20has%20overtaken%20other%20deadly%20cancers%2C%20including%20lung%20and%20breast.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbrueck%40businessinsider.com%20(Hilary%20Brueck)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20losing%20%2420%20billion%20in%20metaverse%2C%20Zuckerberg%20has%20a%20message%20for%20investors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1769682623000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-127771935%2Cimgsize-37166.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fafter-losing-20-billion-in-2025-alone-in-the-business-that-mark-zuckerberg-changed-companys-name-for-meta-tells-investors-dont-expect%2Farticleshow%2F127771935.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meta's%20Reality%20Labs%20division%