20time%20in%20Mexico%20City%20and%20Rio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20headlines%20about%20a%20softening%20job%20market%20began%20to%20stack%20up.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-2026-great-freeze-hiring-layoffs-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20of%20those%20same%20concerns%20still%20dominate%20the%20conversation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20coverage%20of%20layoffs%2C%20hiring%20freezes%2C%20and%20longer%20job%20searches%20became%20more%20common%2C%20I%20put%20my%20foot%20on%20the%20accelerator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20now%20work%20as%20a%20compensation%20analyst%20in%20the%20tech%20sector%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20expand%20my%20search%20to%20find%20this%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c96b21cc-22b9-4b6d-a0af-21bf3906081c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20job%20search%20proved%20to%20be%20more%20difficult%20than%20I%20expected%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrevious%20job%20searches%20had%20taught%20me%20the%20importance%20of%20patience%20and%20resilience.%20It's%20a%20numbers%20game.%20Leverage%20your%20network.%20The%20right%20opportunity%20is%20out%20there.%20I%20appreciated%20those%20general%20truths%20going%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20encountered%20the%20familiar%20dance%20of%20recruiters%20who%20seemed%20enthusiastic%20and%20then%20went%20silent%2C%20I%20was%20prepared%20for%20it.%20Even%20an%20especially%20eye-roll-worthy%20sequence%20with%20an%20exciting%20tech%20company%20didn't%20throw%20me%20off%3A%20an%20interview%20scheduled%20and%20canceled%20at%20the%20last%20minute%2C%20a%20later%20request%20to%20reschedule%2C%20a%20coding%20assignment%20completed%2C%20and%20then%20no%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20proved%20far%20more%20difficult%20was%20the%20uncertainty%20behind%20it%20all.%20I%20couldn't%20tell%20which%20signals%20mattered.%20Was%20the%20job%20market%20softening%20because%20of%20tariffs%3F%20Because%20of%20AI%3F%20Were%20we%20heading%20toward%20a%20recession%3F%20Was%20white-collar%20work%20itself%20undergoing%20a%20more%20permanent%20shift%3F%20Was%20a%20referral%20the%20only%20way%20to%20get%20a%20job%3F%20I%20wasn't%20sure%20what%20information%20to%20anchor%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ea51e026-f1de-458b-9f12-0e69f8d8038f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20became%20clear%20I%20had%20to%20expand%20my%20search%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20New%20York%20City%20at%20the%20time%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20was%20in%20a%20competitive%20job%20market%2C%20but%20I%20also%20assumed%20it%20was%20abundant.%20Even%20if%20there%20were%20millions%20of%20job%20seekers%20in%20New%20York%2C%20I%20thought%20there%20would%20be%20millions%20of%20jobs%20to%20match%20them.%20I%20began%20to%20wonder%20whether%20that%20assumption%20actually%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20I%20would%20find%20my%20next%20role%20in%20New%20York%20had%20been%20a%20fundamental%20part%20of%20my%20decision%20to%20leave%20the%20government%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20the%20signals%20I%20saw%20began%20to%20complicate%20that%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F08%2F13%2Fnyregion%2Fnyc-jobs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20read%20an%20article%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20said%20New%20York%20City%20hadn't%20added%20any%20new%20jobs%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year.%20Having%20just%20left%20a%20role%20analyzing%20job%20gains%20and%20losses%20across%20the%20country%2C%20I%20was%20aware%20of%20how%20uneven%20labor%20markets%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20found%20myself%20thinking%20about%20my%20parents%20and%20how%20often%20they%20had%20moved%20for%20work.%20First%20from%20Nigeria%2C%20and%20then%20multiple%20times%20within%20the%20US%2C%20they%20had%20never%20anchored%20their%20decisions%20to%20a%20single%20city.%20They%20went%20where%20opportunity%20was.%20City%20preference%20came%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20had%20no%20desire%20to%20leave%20New%20Yo