rsation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeter%20Kafka%3A%20This%20is%20a%20story%20that's%20being%20covered%20by%20lots%20of%20different%20sources%2C%20including%20lots%20of%20individuals%20posting%20videos%20from%20their%20phones.%20How%20do%20you%20handle%20reporting%20on%20a%20video%20that%20lots%20of%20people%20have%20already%20seen%2C%20and%20seems%20quite%20clear%3F%20How%20many%20checks%20do%20you%20have%20to%20do%20before%20you%20can%20say%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20happened%26quot%3B%20as%20opposed%20to%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20video%20that%20appears%20to%20show%20this%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKathleen%20Hennessey%3A%20We%20are%20very%20careful.%20We%20know%20that%20a%20video%20that%20appears%20to%20show%20something%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20that%20is%20exactly%20what%20happened.%20Our%20language%20is%20careful.%20And%20we%20recognize%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20have%20every%20single%20video%20first%2C%20obviously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20job%20is%20to%20verify%20it%2C%20and%20to%20watch%20it%20closely%2C%20and%20to%20slow%20it%20down%20a%20thousand%20times%2C%20to%20try%20to%20get%20the%20rights%20to%20it%2C%20and%20to%20call%20the%20lawyers%2C%20and%20figure%20out%20who%20took%20it.%20To%20do%20the%20hard%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20inevitably%2C%20that%20just%20means%20that%20we'll%20be%20slower%20than%20social%20media.%20But%20we'll%20be%20more%20accurate%20and%20more%20careful%20and%20fuller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20you%20say%20to%20readers%20who%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20seeing%20this%20thing%20on%20Reddit%20or%20Instagram.%20Why%20don't%20you%20guys%20have%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20journalist%2C%20it%20never%20feels%20good%20to%20have%20somebody%20send%20you%20an%20account%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BSee%3F%20Look%2C%20this%20is%20what%20happened!%26quot%3B%20And%20you%20have%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20I%20guess%20we're%20not%20quite%20reporting%20it%20that%20way.%20Yet